subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis. This new species resembles
O. obesa Fu, Zhang & Zhang, 2016
by having a similar shaped bulb and RTA (compare Fig. 11B–C and figs 5–6 in
Fu et al. 2016
), but the males can be distinguished by the long and strongly curved embolus ( vs short and slightly curved, compare Figs 11C , 12C with figs 5, 10 in
Fu et al . 2016
), the females can be distinguished by the long connecting tube and the large spermathecae ( vs short and small, respectively, compare Fig. 12E–F with figs 12–13 in
Fu et al . 2016
).
